## Course routes (generic pages, one folder each)

Course pages are shared and parameterized by `level: CourseLevel`. The route file
`app/[lang]/[jlptLevel]/**/page.tsx` awaits the `[jlptLevel]` param and passes it as a
prop; the view reads `lessonId` via `useParams`. Each course view gets its OWN folder with the
page as `index.tsx` (one component = one folder):

| Route | File |
|-------|------|
| `/:level` | `src/features/course/course-page/index.tsx` |
| `/:level/:lessonId` | `src/features/course/lesson-page/index.tsx` |
| `/:level/:lessonId/vocabulary` | `src/features/course/exercise-page/index.tsx` |
| `/:level/:lessonId/grammar` | `src/features/course/grammar-page/index.tsx` |
| `/:level/:lessonId/listening` | `src/features/course/listening-page/index.tsx` |
| `/:level/:lessonId/reading` | `src/features/course/reading-page/index.tsx` |
| `/:level/:lessonId/writing` | `src/features/course/writing-page/index.tsx` |

## Navigation & params (Next, not react-router)

- There is NO `react-router-dom`. Client navigation uses `next/link` (wrapped by
  `LocaleLink`/`LocaleNavLink` in `@/components/locale-link`, which prefix the
  active locale) and the shim hooks in `@/i18n/navigation` (`useParams`,
  `usePathname`, `useLocation`, `useNavigate`). Import route params/pathname from
  `@/i18n/navigation`, never from `react-router-dom`.

## One folder per component / page (IMPORTANT)

- Every component and page lives in its own folder, with the component itself as `index.tsx` (e.g. `src/components/speak-button/index.tsx`, `src/features/course/lesson-page/index.tsx`). Do NOT keep multiple sibling components as flat files in one folder.
- Import a component/page by its folder, extensionless: `import { SpeakButton } from '@/components/speak-button'` (resolves to `.../speak-button/index.tsx`).

## Colocation

- Put a helper used by only ONE page inside that page's folder (e.g. `course/exercise-page/course-quiz.ts`, `course/listening-page/course-listening.ts`). Reference it relatively as a sibling (`./course-quiz.ts`).
- A helper/component shared by SIBLING pages gets its own folder in the shared parent (e.g. `course/choice-button/index.tsx`, `course/shared/index.tsx` for `LessonNotFound`/`ResultScreen`), imported via `@/features/course/...`.
- Shared code for a route segment stays in that segment folder (e.g. `alphabet/alphabet-chart.tsx` for hiragana + katakana).
- Globally reusable UI stays in `src/components/<name>/index.tsx`.
- Colocate a `*.test.ts(x)` next to the file it tests.

## New pages

When adding a route `/foo/bar`, create the view `src/features/foo/bar/index.tsx`
(`'use client'`) and the route file `app/[lang]/foo/bar/page.tsx` (server:
`generateStaticParams` + `generateMetadata` + render the view; wrap in
`<ClientOnly>` if interactive). Register the logical path in
`src/constants/routes.ts` (or a `*_SITEMAP_PATHS` array) so `app/sitemap.ts`
includes it. Add param-generation helpers in `@/i18n/route-helpers` when the
route has dynamic segments.

## Imports

Prefer `@/features/...` and `@/components/...` path aliases (extensionless for folder-based components/pages). Use relative imports only for siblings in the same folder.
